                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13875.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Bonney</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">San Luis Potosi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>San Luis Potosí is now the temporary capital of Mexico. Convention troops have
                    advanced easterly and southerly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bonney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
